21/12/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Boris Trajkovski, Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski, Interior Minister Hari Kostov and Democratic Union of Integration leader Ali Ahmeti met on Friday (19 December) with relatives of the 12 Macedonians and six ethnic Albanians missing since the 2001 military conflict.
The families expressed strong dissatisfaction with the course of investigation into the fate of their relatives.
All parties agreed to hold another meeting at the end of January.
Jeffrey Binger, chief of the International Commission on Missing Persons in Macedonia, also attended the meeting.
Earlier, he commented that the government lacks the political will to tackle the problem.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 20/12/03;
MIA, A1 TV - 19/12/03)
